messages.text: Hey, are you there?
Why won’t you talk to me? Are you mad?
What’s going on?
5 minutes later
This isn’t funny. Stop it.
What are you talking about?
Whoever this is…if you text me again, I’ll call the cops.
Whoa, Jill, chill out. It’s Aly. Your best friend, remember?
What’s with you?
This isn’t Aly. This is someone trying to play a sick prank on me.
What’s going on?
I get that you’ve been spending time with your boyfriend, but you can’t just ignore your best friend.
Don’t you dare bring Danny into this.
Woah…aggressive much? What’s the matter with you?
You’re not Aly. She died last week.
Okay, now you’re the one who needs to stop pranking me.
No, she’s really dead. Her funeral is tomorrow.
That’s way too dark of a joke, Jill. Even for you.
It’s not a joke. But I wish it was — more than anything.
Aly is dead, and you’re just some weirdo pretending to be her. I’m calling the cops for real.
I swear it’s me!
I can prove it—
When we were little, you used to water rocks because you thought they would grow.
A lot of people knew that.
Yes, but you named your favorite rock after your crush.
And you thought if you watered the rock, it would make your crush fall in love with you.
I was the only person who knew that.
And I never told anyone. I swore I wouldn’t.
Do you believe me now?
Aly?
Yes! It’s me!
But…HOW??
Where are you??
I’m here, in my house. I mean, at least, I think I am?
Do you think I’m actually alive?
Not possible — they found your corpse last Tuesday.
You were supposed to meet up with Danny to work on your science project.
I remember…going to meet him…
Really? Are you sure you didn’t forget you had plans?
Because they found you on the trail, where you used to go running.
You slipped and hit your head.
I don’t…I don’t remember any of that…
Just try, Aly. Try to remember.
But I didn’t go running…
Jill, I feel weird…every time I think about that day…
It’s like the world spins.
No, Aly. You’ve got to keep pushing yourself—
You’ve got to remember.
Maybe we can find out what really happened.
Jill…
2 minutes later
Aly? Aly, are you still there??
I remember now…
What?! What do you remember?
Where are you right now?
I’m at Danny’s. Why?
Where is he? Is he with you?
No, he went out to pick up food. He’ll be back any minute.
You have to get out of there—
It all makes sense now.
What’s going on?
Just trust me, okay? You have to leave Danny’s right now!
Before he gets back!
You’ve always had a problem with Danny.
But he’s the only reason I’ve made it through the last week.
I’m not going to just leave him because a ghost wants me to.
You’re probably not even real.
No, listen to me. I remember everything now.
And the reason I’m still here…it must be to warn you.
SO GET OUT OF THERE — NOW!
Tell me what you remember.
Don’t you trust me?
I trusted my best friend, of course…
But I think I’m having a very realistic hallucination. I don’t trust myself.
Okay, I’ll tell you what happened. That day I died…I didn’t go running.
I actually met up with Danny. I remember it.
No, that’s not right. Danny said you never showed up.
He lied.
I was at his house. We were working on our project in the basement.
No, that can’t be.
He got up to use the bathroom. He left his phone.
And you looked through it?
Of course. You know how nosy I am.
And like you said, I never liked him. I always suspected that…
What? What did you find?
He was texting another girl.
He was cheating on you.
But…that can’t be true…
I’m sorry, Jill.
I took his phone. I was going to leave and show you the texts.
I was cutting through the trail on my way home, but…
He caught up with me.
No. Stop.
We got into a fight.
He wanted his phone back.
I wouldn’t give it to him.
I tried to get away from him, but—
Please don’t say it.
But he hit me with something.
Right on the head.
And that’s the last thing I remember…
Jill, I think that’s why I’m still here. Because he killed me.
And got away with it.
Please, I need to save you—
You have to leave his house before he gets back.
Why should I believe you?
Because your life depends on it.
Wait, I can prove I was with Danny that day too—
I was in a rush to leave on Tuesday.
I’m pretty sure I accidentally grabbed his science book, instead of mine.
Remember how mine has all those doodles in it that we made together?
Yeah…
Go check his backpack.
I’m sure he didn’t notice.
If my book’s there, Jill…
You’ll know what he did.
This is crazy…
But okay. I’ll check.
1 minute later
Well??
I had to go up to his room. Looking now…
OMG—
Aly, it’s here. Your book is here.
OMG, I’m so sorry I didn’t believe you.
It’s okay. Just get out of there now!
HURRY!
But this book is evidence of what he did.
I have to give it to the police.
Do it after you leave his house!
Take the book with you and RUN!
Okay, I’m leaving now…
Stop texting! Let me know when you’re out!
Oh no…
Aly, he’s back. I just heard the door.
Climb out the window!
GET OUT OF THERE!
It’s too high!
He’s looking for me…
What do I do??
Help me!
Okay, forget this whole thing—
Just tell him you aren’t feeling well and then go home.
You’ll have to leave the book, but at least you’ll be safe.
That’s all that matters now.
3 minutes later
Jill?
Jill, what’s happening??
ANSWER ME!
He found me in his room!
I was trying to hide the book somewhere, but he found me.
He came after me, but I locked myself in the bathroom.
Wait, does he know it’s my book?
Yeah. And he knows I know EVERYTHING—
I could see it in his face.
Okay, stay in the bathroom. Let me think…
Aly, he’s trying to break down the door!
OMG, call the cops!
I did! They’re sending someone, but what if they don’t make it in time?
There’s no other way out of this bathroom…
What do I do?? He’s going to get in!
It’s okay, Jill. It’ll all be okay.
I’m here for you. I always will be.
How, Aly??
I’m so scared!
At least I’ll be seeing you soon…
4 minutes later
Aly?? Are you still there?
Please don’t leave me now!
Wait — Danny stopped slamming into the door.
He’s…talking to someone.
He sounds so scared.
He’s saying, “This is impossible. It can’t be you. You’re dead.”
Aly?
OMG, he’s running away!
I hear the sirens — the cops are here!
They caught him, Aly.
They caught him!
Aly?
10 minutes later
Aly, I know it was you.
You somehow appeared and scared Danny away.
Thank you for saving me. For everything.
I guess…you must be gone now.
You did what you were sticking around to do.
You saved my life.
Listen, I know I’m too old for rocks now, Aly…
But I’m going to find a new one to keep in my room.
Just like you said, it’ll always be with me…
Because I’m naming it after you.
